loop DocsSweep(repo):
  goal: documentation accurately reflects current implementation
  context:
    read codebase, README, docs, examples, changelog, and repository guidance
  authority:
    may edit documentation and examples
    may not change product behavior, public APIs, tests, secrets, or deployment configuration
  cycle:
    observe: find one stale, missing, or misleading documentation area
    act: update the smallest coherent documentation section
    verify:
      run doc checks, link checks, examples, and relevant tests when available
    decide:
      keep if: docs are more accurate and checks pass
      revert if: checks fail, examples break, or product behavior changes
      escalate if: product behavior is ambiguous or authority is insufficient
  stop:
    success if: no material documentation drift remains
    no_op if: docs already match implementation
    stall if: two passes find no new actionable drift
    budget if: iteration, time, or token budget is reached
    blocked if: current behavior cannot be determined
  return:
    changed files, evidence, remaining uncertainties, and PR summary

